    <element name="Mechanical Rhythms" type="Class Feature" source="BloxBoss6's Homebrew" id="ID_BLOXBOSS6_BB6H_CLASS_FEATURE_ELDRITCH_MECHANICAL_RHYTHMS">
        <supports>Eldritch Invocation, Pact of Gond</supports>
        <prerequisite>5th level, Pact of Gond feature</prerequisite>
        <requirements>[level:5],ID_BLOXBOSS6_BB6H_CLASS_FEATURE_WARLOCK_PACT_BOON_PACT_OF_GOND</requirements>
        <description>
            <p class="flavor">Prerequisite: 5th level, Pact of Gond feature</p>
            <p>Once per turn when you hit a creature with your pact weapon, you can expend a warlock spell slot to deal an extra 1d8 force damage to the target, plus another 1d8 per level of the spell slot, and you can knock the target prone if it is Huge or smaller.</p>
        </description>
        <sheet>
            <description>Once per turn when you hit a creature with your pact weapon, you can expend a warlock spell slot to deal an extra 1d8 force damage to the target, plus another 1d8 per level of the spell slot, and you can knock the target prone if it is Huge or smaller.</description>
        </sheet>
    </element>

    <element name="Improved Pact Tool" type="Class Feature" source="BloxBoss6's Homebrew" id="ID_BLOXBOSS6_BB6H_CLASS_FEATURE_ELDRITCH_IMPROVED_PACT_TOOL">
        <supports>Eldritch Invocation, Pact of Gond</supports>
        <prerequisite>7th level, Pact of Gond feature</prerequisite>
        <requirements>[level:7],ID_BLOXBOSS6_BB6H_CLASS_FEATURE_WARLOCK_PACT_BOON_PACT_OF_GOND</requirements>
        <description>
            <p class="flavor">Prerequisite: 7th level, Pact of Gond feature</p>
            <p>You can use any tool summon with your Pact of Gond feature as a spellcasting focus for your warlock spells.</p>
            <p class="indent">In addition, the tool gains a +1 bonus to its attack and damage rolls, unless it is a magic tool that already has a bonus to those rolls.</p>
        </description>
        <sheet>
            <description>You can use any tool summon with your Pact of Gond feature as a spellcasting focus for your warlock spells.
            In addition, the tool gains a +1 bonus to its attack and damage rolls, unless it is a magic tool that already has a bonus to those rolls.</description>
        </sheet>
    </element>

